recipe: Rinse poha once and let it soften for 5 minutes.
Heat oil, sauté onions and potatoes until soft.
Add peanuts and roast lightly.
Mix in poha gently, cook covered for 2–3 minutes.
Crumble paneer finely and keep aside.
Cook onion and tomato till soft.
Add paneer and cook for 4–5 minutes.
Serve with freshly cooked rotis.
Marinate chicken in curd for 20 minutes.
Grill or pan-cook till fully cooked.
Boil rice separately until soft.
Serve chicken over rice.
